<https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/53001557/2025-26/evaluation> a ns1:EvaluationSystem ;
    ns1:evaluationDescription """The evaluation of the course will have two components. On the one hand, it will be carried out by means of continuous evaluation. At this regard, student will be asked to do three compulsory practical lessons and to deliver one homework project. The homework will consist on the design and implementation of a digital system on VHDL using a commercial FPGA. The goal is to strengthen the basic theoretical and practical knowledge of the students. The work will be done in groups of two students, having until the day of the final exam to finish it.
On the other hand, there will be a final written exam that will be used to assess the capacity of the students to solve problems in the area of digital electronics and microprocessors.
The final mark of the course will be computed as follows:
If the student passes the final exam (a minimum of a 5 is obtained): 50% Final Exam + 50% VHDL Project
If the student fails the final exam: 100% Final Exam"""@es ;
    ns1:hasEvaluationTrial <https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/53001557/2025-26/evaluation/trial1>,
        <https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/53001557/2025-26/evaluation/trial2>,
